The paper deals with video semantic segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves the use of clock signals to schedule the processing of different layers, which is a technique commonly used in neural network architectures (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of data-driven clocks, which suggests the use of machine learning algorithms (cs.AI). The datasets used for evaluation are video datasets, indicating the use of multimedia techniques (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the clockwork convnets, which suggests the use of optimization techniques (cs.NE).
